column8: If unknown whether participant served in military, alert if they say they have obtained care from a VA facility
column9: If MEDVA=1 then SERVED should not equal 9
column10: If Q16. MEDVA (VA medical care) = 1 (Yes) then Q15. SERVED (served in armed forces) should not equal 9 (Don't know),it should be equal to 1 (Yes)
column11: IF MEDVA=1 and SERVED=9

column8: Age of onset is not older than age of participant at visit
column9: BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, and BEREMAGO should be less than or equal to the age of participant at visit
column10: BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, and BEREMAGO (age of onset) should be less than or equal to age at visit
column11: If BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, or BEREMAGO >  (FRMDATEB9 - BIRTHMO|1|BIRTHYR)/365.25
column13: BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, BEREMAGO, BIRTHMO, BIRTHYR

column8: BIRTHMO aligns with birth month from UDSv3
column9: UDSv4 BIRTHMO should equal UDSv3 BIRTHMO
column10: UDSv4 Q1a. BIRTHMO (participant birth month) should equal UDSv3 Q6a. BIRTHMO
column11: If UDSv4 BIRTHMO ≠ UDSv3 BIRTHMO

column8: BIRTHYR aligns with birth year from UDSv3
column9: UDSv4 BIRTHYR should equal UDSv3 BIRTHYR
column10: UDSv4 Q1a. BIRTHYR(participant birth year) should equal UDSv3 Q6a. BIRTHYR
column11: If UDSv4 BIRTHYR ≠ UDSv3 BIRTHYR

column8: BIRTHSEX aligns with SEX from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 SEX = 1, then UDSv4 BIRTHSEX should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 SEX = 1 (male), then UDSv4 BIRTHSEX (sex assigned at birth) should equal 1 (male)
column11: If UDSv3 SEX = 1 and UDSv4 BIRTHSEX  = 2

column8: BIRTHSEX aligns with SEX from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 SEX = 2, then UDSv4 BIRTHSEX should equal 2
column10: If UDSv3 SEX = 2 (female), then UDSv4 BIRTHSEX (sex assigned at birth) should equal 2 (female)
column11: If UDSv3 SEX = 2 and UDSv4 BIRTHSEX  = 1

column8: Age of onset is not older than age of participant at visit
column9: BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, and BEREMAGO should be less than or equal to the age of participant at visit
column10: Form B9 QBEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, and BEREMAGO (age of onset) should be less than or equal to age at visit
column11: IF BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, or BEREMAGO >  (FRMDATEB9 - BIRTHMO|1|BIRTHYR)/365.25
column13: BEHAGE, COGAGE, PERCHAGE, MOTORAGE, PSYCHAGE, BEREMAGO, BIRTHMO, BIRTHYR

column8: Living situation aligns with marital status
column9: If MARISTAT=5 then LIVSITUA should not equal 2
column10: If Q11. MARITSTAT (Marital status)=5 (Never married) then Q12. LIVSITUA (Living situation) should not equal 2 (Lives with spouse or partner)
column11: IF MARISTAT=5 and LIVSITUA=2

column8: Living situation aligns with marital status
column9: If MARISTAT in (1,6)  then LIVSITUA should equal 2
column10: If Q11. MARITSTAT (Marital status) in (1,6) (Married or living as married) then Q12. LIVSITUA (Living situation) should equal 2 (Lives with spouse or partner)
column11: IF MARISTAT in (1,6) and LIVSITUA ne 2

column8: Primary residence aligns with living situation
column9: If LIVSITUA=1 then RESIDENC should not equal 4
column10: If Q12. LIVSITUA (Living situation) =1 (Lives alone) then Q13. (Primary residence) should not equal 4 (skilled nursing facility, nursing home, hospital, or hospice)
column11: If LIVSITUA=1 and RESIDENC=4

column8: Primary residence aligns with living situation
column9: If LIVSITUA=6 then RESIDENC should not equal 1
column10: If Q12. LIVSITUA (Living situation) =6 (Live in group home (e.g., assisted living, nursing home, convent)) then Q13. (Primary residence) should not equal 1 (Single– or multi–family private residence)
column11: If LIVSITUA=6 and RESIDENC=1

column8: Primary residence aligns with living situation
column9: If LIVSITUA ne 6 then RESIDENC should not equal 3 or 4
column10: If Q12. LIVSITUA (Living situation) ne 6 (Live in group home (e.g., assisted living, nursing home, convent)) then Q13. (Primary residence) should not equal  3or 4 (Assisted living or skilled nursing facility, nursing home, hospital, or hospice)
column11: If LIVSITUA=1 and RESIDENC=4

column8: ETHISPANIC aligns with HISPANIC from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 HISPANIC = 1, then UDSv4 ETHISPANIC should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q8. HISPANIC (Hispanic/Latino ethnicity) = 1, then UDSv4 Q3d. ETHISPANIC (Race--Hispanic or Latino) should equal 1
column11: If UDSv3 HISPANIC = 1 and UDSv4 ETHISPANIC ne 1

column8: RACEAIAN aligns with RACE, RACESEC, and RACETER from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 RACERACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 3, then UDSv4 RACEAIAN should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q9-11. RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 3 (american indian or alaska native), then UDSv4  Q3a. RACEAIAN (Race--American Indian or Alaska Native) should equal 1
column11: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 3 and UDSv4 RACEAIAN ne 1

column8: RACEASIAN aligns with RACERACE, RACESEC, and RACETER from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 5, then UDSv4 RACEASIAN should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q9-11. RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 5 (asian), then UDSv4  Q3b. RACEAIAN (Race--Asian) should equal 1
column11: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 5 and UDSv4 RACEASIAN ne 1

column8: RACEBLACK aligns with RACERACE, RACESEC, and RACETER from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 2, then UDSv4 RACEBLACK should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q9-11. RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 2 (black or african american), then UDSv4  Q3c. RACEBLACK (Race--Black or African American) should equal 1
column11: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 2 and UDSv4 RACEBLACK ne 1

column8: RACENHPI aligns with RACERACE, RACESEC, and RACETER from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 4, then UDSv4 RACENHPI  should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q9-11. RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 4 (native hawaiian or other pacific islander), then UDSv4  Q3f. RACENHPI (Race--Native Hawaiian or Pacific Islander) should equal 1
column11: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 4 and UDSv4 RACENHPI ne 1

column8: RACEWHITE aligns with RACERACE, RACESEC, and RACETER from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 1, then UDSv4 RACEWHITE should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q9-11. RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 1 (white), then UDSv4  Q3g. RACEWHITE (Race--White) should equal 1
column11: If UDSv3 RACE, RACESEC, or RACETER = 1 and UDSv4 RACEWHITE ne 1

column8: PREDOMLAN aligns with PRIMLANG from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 PRIMLANG = 1, then UDSv4 PREDOMLAN  should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q12. PRIMLANG = 1 (English), then UDSv4  Q8. PREDOMLAN (Primary language) should equal 1 (English)
column11: If UDSv3 PRIMLANG = 1 and UDSv4 PREDOMLAN ≠ 1

column8: PREDOMLAN aligns with PRIMLANG from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 PRIMLANG = 2, then UDSv4 PREDOMLAN  should equal 2
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q12. PRIMLANG = 2 (Spanish), then UDSv4  Q8. PREDOMLAN (Primary language) should equal 2 (Spanish)
column11: If UDSv3 PRIMLANG = 2 and UDSv4 PREDOMLAN ≠ 2

column8: EDUC should be greater than or equal to EDUC from UDSv3
column9: UDSv4 EDUC should be greater than or equal to UDSv3 EDUC
column10: UDSv4 Q10a. EDUC (years of education) should be greater than or equal to UDSv3 IVP Q13. EDUC (years of education)
column11: If UDSv4 EDUC < UDSv3 EDUC

column8: HANDED aligns with HANDED from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 HANDED = 1, then UDSv4 HANDED should equal 1
column10: If UDSv3 IVP Q12. HANDED = 1 (Left handed), then UDSv4  Q8. HANDED should equal 1 (Left handed)
column11: If UDSv3 HANDED = 1 and UDSv4 HANDED ≠ 1

column8: HANDED aligns with HANDED from UDSv3
column9: If UDSv3 HANDED = 2, then UDSv4 HANDED should equal 2
column10: If UDSv3 Q19. HANDED (Are you left- or right-handed?) = 2 (right handed), then UDSv4  Q9. HANDED should equal 2 (Right handed)
column11: If UDSv3 HANDED = 2 and UDSv4 HANDED ≠ 2

column8: Martial status aligns across visits
column9: If UDSv3 MARISTAT in (1,2,3,4) at PREVVISIT then UDSv4 MARISTAT should not equal 5
column10: If UDSv3 FVP Q4. MARISTAT in (1,2,3,4) (Married, widowed, divorced, or separated) at PREVVISIT then UDSv4 MARISTAT should not equal 5 (never married)
column11: If UDSv3 MARISTAT in (1,2,3,4) at PREVVISIT and  UDSv4 MARISTAT=5

column8: LIVSITUA co-participant living situation INLIVWTH
column9: IF INRELTO=1 and INLIVWTH=1 then LIVSITUA must equal 2
column10: IF Form A2, Q1. INRELTO (relationship to participant)=1 (spouse, partner, companion) and Form A2, Q3. INLIVWTH (lives with participant?)=1 (yes) then Q12. LIVSITUA (participant's living situation) should not equal 2 (lives with one other person: spouse or partner)
column11: IF (INRELTO=1 and INLIVWTH=1) and LIVSITUA ne 2

column8: LIVSITUA co-participant living situation INLIVWTH
column9: IF INRELTO=1 and INLIVWTH=0 then LIVSITUA cannot equal 2
column10: IF Form A2, Q1. INRELTO (relationship to participant)=1 (spouse, partner, companion) and Form A2, Q3. INLIVWTH (lives with participant?)=0 (no) then Q12. LIVSITUA (participant's living situation) cannot equal 2 (lives with one other person: spouse or partner)
column11: IF (INRELTO=1 and INLIVWTH=1) and LIVSITUA=2
